Add a V1 UI-toolkit primitive that renders a DYNAMIC LIST from a signal
holding a JSON ARRAY string, with per-item field access + conditional
styling — so a chat message thread (left/right role bubbles) can be
authored DECLARATIVELY instead of by hand-written JS. This closes the gap
that forKeyed needs a real Signal[List[A]] while computedSignal / fetch
signals only produce Signal[String], and _ssc_ui_arrayValue does NOT parse
JSON — so a JSON-array-in-a-string could not feed forKeyed.

API (std.ui.reactive / std.ui.primitives):
- forJson(items: Signal[String], key: String)(render: Any => TkNode): TkNode
  — JSON.parses `items` at render + on every change, keys each row by the
  item FIELD `key` (index fallback), calls `render` with the parsed item.
- itemField(item: Any, name: String): String — read a row field as text
  ('' when absent/null); use it for text and to branch per-item styling.

Layers, mirroring forKeyed at every step:
- reactive.ssc forJson constructor -> ForJsonNode (nodes.ssc) -> lower.ssc
  case forJsonView(items, key, item => lower(render(item))); forJsonView +
  itemField extern defs in primitives.ssc (auto-mapped to _ssc_ui_* in JS).
- signals.mjs: _ssc_ui_forJsonView / _ssc_ui_itemField builders,
  _ssc_ui_jsonArray (parse array string) + _ssc_ui_jsonKey helpers, a
  _ForJson SSR render case (data-ssc-forjson, per-row data-ssc-key), and
  _mountForJson — the JSON-string sibling of _mountKeyed's keyed reconcile
  (surviving rows keep their DOM), dispatched from _mountKeyed.
- Interpreter/JVM parity (FrontendIntrinsics, JvmRuntimeUiPrimitives,
  JvmGen import, JsGen hasUiHelpers): the browser runtime is authoritative
  (like forKeyedView), JVM fallback renders empty. NOT recompiled here —
  emit-spa uses the JS path + auto-mapped externs, so source .ssc + the
  staged signals.mjs suffice; rebuild via sbt before relying on the JVM path.

Proven end-to-end: emit-spa --frontend react -> headless Chrome. Initial
JSON array renders 2 bubbles (user right/blue, bot left/grey); clicking a
button that sets the signal to a longer array reconciles in a 3rd user
bubble (right/blue) reactively. See examples/frontend/forjson-chat-demo.
